metadata.name: Gold X Mining Corp
metadata.description: Gold X Mining Corp., a junior mining company, engages in developing the Toroparu Gold Project in Guyana, South America. Its Toroparu project comprises 100% owned Upper Puruni Concession, which covers an area of 53,844 hectares located in the Cuyuni-Mazaruni Region of Western Guyana. The company also holds Chicharron Project located in the Segovia mining title. The company was formerly known as Sandspring Resources Ltd. and changed its name to Gold X Mining Corp. in November 2019. Gold X Mining Corp. was founded in 2006 and is based in Vancouver, Canada.
